The paper deals with entity linking, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), making cs.CL and cs.IR the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach that uses graph algorithms, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The approach also involves structured knowledge bases, which are typically stored in databases (cs.DB), and the paper evaluates the approach using performance metrics (cs.LG).
